# Code Quality Standards

This project follows the Code Quality standard documented in `standards/CODE-QUALITY.md`.

## Verification

Before claiming done:
1. Test scripts work on Windows (PowerShell)
2. Verify templates are fillable (have placeholders)
3. Check documentation is complete

## Documentation Style

- Use tables for structured data
- Include "why" explanations, not just "how"
- Provide examples where helpful
- Keep files scannable (headers, bullets, tables)

## Template Quality

Templates must be:
- Generic (no project-specific content)
- Fillable (clear `[placeholder]` markers)
- Complete (all sections present)
- Consistent (same structure across files)

## Script Quality

Scripts must:
- Work on target platform without errors
- Have help text (`-h` or `--help`)
- Use colored output for clarity
- Handle existing files gracefully (`-Force` flag)
